    /*
    ... (Shock) Sorry, I just don't think I've ever seen you in anything but your normal getup. Do you always wear less clothes during summer? 

    It's always important to regulate your body temperature through these heatwaves. Say, are you free later? We could always go cool down by the beach if you're interested. 
    Err, as a doctor wanting the best for his patient, of course. 

    Y'know, the key to lowering your chances of melanoma are sunscreen and thin layers of clothing, especially with you being outside most of the day. 
    Speaking of, do you ever take a break? You can always stop by the clinic for some AC and some electrolytes if needed.

    Hey, I was looking through your files earlier and hope you don't mind that I... Err, I adjusted it a bit. Just some doctor jargon, nothing to worry about, promise. 

    I know it gets hot down here in the valley, but make sure you're keeping your windows closed at night, yeah?
    Why? Oh... Uh, contrary to popular belief, drafts, especially when you're sleeping, can be detrimental to your health! 
    Just trust me...

    Oh, I thought you'd show up today! Here, I made extra just for you. [253] // triple shot espresso

    Oh, your face is so red and flushed, hold on, let me check your heart rate. 
    ...
    Hmm... You aren't overextering yourself, are you? You know people die every day due to not taking proper precautions in summer. 
    Here, this should help you cool down. [873] // pina colada

    It's awfully hot today, isn't it?
    Make sure you're wearing enough sunscreen. I wouldn't want that beautiful skin to--
    Err, I mean, I just wouldn't want you to get a sunburn is all.

    Here, I thought you might like one of these... I found one over by the playground and thought it'd look good in your ha- [402] 
    Err... Sorry, Just--Traditinally, lathyrus odoratus --err--sweet peas were used for wound dressings and for their anti-inflamatory benefits.
    I thought it might help you stay safer when you're down in the mines. Albiet against medical advice, but...

    Hey, I've been meaning to ask you: do you think I could get a spare key to your house? It'll just be for medical emergencies -- I have them for all my patients. 
    I wouldn't want something to happen to you and you be all alone... 

    I've been doing some reading into electroconvulsive therapy. Interesting stuff, I might say...
    Though, some patients have been known to become more docile and suffer memory losses... 
    Hm? What is electroconvulsive therapy?
    Oh, shock therapy.
    Why? Interested in a few sessions? Hm, it might help with the depression you might feel being alone all the time on that farm...

    Oh, hold still.
    %Harvey lifts your chin, inspecting your jaw and neck. He plucks a leaf from inside the collar of your shirt out.
    Just needed to make sure everything's fine. Many things can be missed, y'know?

    Have you been up to the bathhouse yet?
    It might help some of those aches and pains you might have doing all that farmwork. 
    */
