    /*
    I've been interested in learning more about the psychology aspect of medicine, but...
    Ugh, the library here really isn't the best for that.
    Maybe I should pay a visit to zuzu city soon...

    Have you ever heard of the milgram experiment?
    Well, to cut things short, it essentially tested the willingness of participants to obey an authority figure despite conflicts with their conscience.
    ...
    Do you think you'd follow someone, despite the heinous things they might ask you to do, petname? 

    I was doing some reading the other day and stumbled upon a few books about the 'dancing plague.'
    Apparently contemporaries blamed 'divine punishment' or 'hot blood' for the mass hysteria that happened in 1518. 
    While the doctor part of me wants to blame potential ergot poisoning and just plain religious fears... I can't help but think divine punishment shows itself in mysterious ways, don't you agree?

    How are you faring lately? You aren't over exterting yourself, are you? 
    I worry about you, dealing with that illness and doing all this hard farmwork when the heat is bearing down...

    We should have a safeword when you call me, so I know when you're okay vs. when you need help... You know I'd be there in a heartbeat to take care of you, petname.
    Err... As your doctor that is.

    Ugh, all this heat is making me sweat up a storm. I don't know how others can maintain facial hair, it all just... accumulates.
    Do you think I should shave it? Maybe it's time for something new...

    ...
    Have you been running around this entire time without sunscreen? You look red.
    Ugh, come on, I'll take you to an exam room to help you apply some since you clearly can't do it on your own.

    Oh, I didn't think I'd get a chance to see you today! 
    Well, since you're here, I think I could fit you in for a little checkup. How are you feeling with your disease and all?
    Is the heat having an effect on you at all?

    Y'know, long exposure to the sun can cause dizziness. 
    If you ever need to lay down, you're more than welcome to in my be--Err, the clinic.
    Just tell Maru I let you. 

    Just because it's summer doesn't mean you can't get sick.
    I've seen some of the stuff you do on that farm, petname. You should really wash your hands more often, given your condition and all.

    Yoba, this heat is killing me. I could really use an iced coffee right about now. 
    Hm... Wouldn't that be nice? Having a coffee shop here in the valley?

    I know I should be grateful for the lack of illness in summer, but I can't help but worry for some of my patients. 
    Take George for example, I'm sure his knees are killing him right about now. 
    Hm, speaking of, are you growing any peppers? I'm sure they'd help out with their natural pain-relief properties. 

    Have you a radio on that farm yet, petname? You should really look into getting one. 
    I swear, summer skies are the best kind to listen in to, especially for planes. There's no interference from any clouds.

    Have you seen any fireflies out yet? They love to come out during cool summer nights.
    I guess I should show you my favorite spot someday, yeah? It could be a date! Err... A casual meeting between a doctor and their patient, yeah?
    */

