    /*
    You know, you shouldn't be out in the sun for too long, petname. I know you wanted to see me, but it's not worth risking your health for that. 

    Hey, I heard these were great aphrodisiacs.[421] Maybe we can test that theory at your next appointment, yeah?

    Y'know, next time you decide to be a brat at your checkup, I'll pull out the medical-grade restraints. 
    Ain't no reason to stick your tongue out and lick me like that...

    I know it's hot out, but you should really cover up. Thin layers are the key to preventing heat stroke out here.
    Plus, it's not only the sun's gaze you have to be weary of...

    %You overhear Harvey mumbling about new pieces of MRI and CT technology that he can't quite afford.
    Oh, @. Sorry, I was just mumbling to myself how city doctors always get all this new, less-invasive and "safe" procedural tech, but...
    I don't know, there's just something about doing things the old-fashioned way, right, petname?

    Have you been taking your medicines lately?_Yes._Good {{Name}}. Keep it up and I might reward you at our next appointment._...Maybe_Don't lie to me, petname. I'll shove the pills down your throat if need be.

    You look flushed in this heat. Do you want me to escort you home?
    I could conduct a home exam if you need...

    I can't believe it's almost been half a year already. How does the saying go? 
    I guess time really does fly when you do the things you love?
    
    Has anyone ever told you you're just like summer, petname?
    Warm and bright, yet fleeting. Let me cherish these moments with you, yeah? I'm not getting any younger...

    Even though it gets pretty hot here during summer, visiting the bathhouse every once in a while is still good for your health. 
    Something about the benefits of saunas have caused even some patients of mine to miraculously regain some lost mobility in their extremeties. 
    If you'd like, I could go with you. I could use some pain relief myself. 

    Have you been harvesting honey with all the flowers you're growing? 
    I'm sure Vincent would like some. It's my secret to getting him to take cough medicine whenever he comes in with a cold. 

    ...$l#$b#Hm? Oh, my cheeks are red?
    Sorry, it must be the summer heat making me feel a little woozy.

    Seeing you run around town makes me remember my college days. I had so much energy back then, I honestly miss having knees that didn't ache all the time.
    I don't miss it for the life of me though, it wasn't until I was older that I got to meet you, after all. 

    Mmm... Hold on, you don't look too well. Say 'ahh' for me, petname. I need to make sure you don't have heatstroke... or something worse. 
    ...
    You look fine, for now. Take it easy or I'll force you to relax in the clinic. 
    */

