    /*
    Hey, don't forget flu season's starting soon. Make sure you swing by and get yourself a flu shot, yeah?
    
    Ugh, fall being around makes me remember all the times Alex came to me with a concussion after his gridball practices. I'm so glad he stopped, but between you and me, the business was nice...
    
    Brrr... It's always so chilly this time of year. Make sure you cover up. Doctor's orders.

    I can't believe how quickly the seasons have been changing this year. I can't believe it's already fall and I've yet to really get to know you.
    Say, why don't we get a drink at Gus' sometime? We can err...
    Discuss your medical record or something...

    Hmm... Hold out your hands for me.
    %Harvey runs his hands along your calloused hands, months of farmwork truly showing for the first time. 
    ...
    As I thought. Make sure you're taking care of these. It can get worse.

    Fall's probably the busiest season for you, yeah?
    Well, if you ever need extra energy tonics, I'd be happy to write a personalized prescription for you. 

    Ugh, I tried changing my morning routine and adding some pumpkin spice to go along with the seasonal trends but...
    ... Ugh.
    I think I'll just stick to my normal cup of plain coffee...

    Y'know, I keep seeing you run around without a jacket. As a doctor, I have to advise against that. 
    Here, you could have mine for now, but seriously, bundle up more. Doctor's orders. [(S)1018] 

    I know you're the type to forage a lot, so be careful while you're out there, yeah?
    While fall is the time for a lot of mushrooms, there's been many cases of people mistaking the good ones from the bad ones. 

    In a pinch, blackberry leaves can be used as a gargle for mouth and throat inflamation. 
    But... Don't get any ideas, please. Due to the high levels of tannins, it can cause nausea and vomiting. 
    If you have a cold or just a sore throat, you should always stop by the clinic. The stuff I have in here works a hell of a lot better. 

    Say, have you found any hazelnut lately? It makes a wonderful addition to coffee when roasted. 
    I'll have to brew you some whenever I get my hands on it, the flavor's to die for. 

    That'll be the last time I try one of their "new and better fall flavors!". 
    I'm so tired of falling for all the same gimicks these coffee companies run on their products.
    It tasted like dirt. Such a shame to put good coffee beans to waste like that... 

    Make sure you're keeping your windows closed and locked at night. With this type of weather, I fear the slightest breeze could trigger a cold. 
    Though I'd love the business, I'd hate to see someone as {{LDescript}} as you sick. 

    %You overheard Harvey mumbling something about lost medical records and patient's perscriptions. Maybe it's best you leave him alone to actually work today. 
    */

