    /*
    %You overhear Harvey mumbling to himself.
    Hm, oh, sorry petname. I just...
    Ugh, I have so much work to do this time of year, it being flu season and all. Why don't you keep me company for a bit?

    Oh, hold on. You look...
    %Harvey presses his fingers to your throat, feeling for any abnormalities.
    Do me a favor, say 'ahh'.
    Mmm. Just what I thought. You need some rest, you look like you might come down with a cold if you don't bundle up, petname. 

    I could really go for a cup of coffee right now... Ugh, there's nothing better than a fresh cup on a cold day like this.
    Speaking of, I was just about to go put another pot of my favorite brew on, would you like some?

    You aren't still going into the mines, are you? 
    Petname, you know better than that. You could risk making your condition worse. 
    At least tell me before you go down, yeah? That way I can stock up on extra supplies when I sa-
    Err... If you come into the office afterwards. 

    Make sure you're still maintaining a good diet, petname.
    I know treats like Gus' pizza are good for its price, but make sure you're still eating veggies. You can't indulge in too much greasy food in your condition. 

    I know you're growing a few pumpkins on your farm, if you intend to carve them please be careful, I wouldn't want you cutting yourself on accident.
    You can always bring them to me, I mean, believe it or not I know my way around a bone saw, so how hard could a carving knife be?

    All this labwork I've been doing has really been making my head spin.
    I think it's the loneliness making it worse, honestly. 
    Say, why don't you come and keep me company one of these days? It'd make it a hell of a lot more enjoyable running your results with you there next to me.
    
    Y'know, it's a little too cold to be wearing something like that, especially with your disease. 
    Go back home and bundle up. As your doctor, the last thing I want is for you to get worse. 

    Ugh, sometimes I think about moving to the city for a better chance at a successful clinic, but...
    ...
    I don't know, something about a peaceful life on a farm has been drawing me back into staying. 

    Tch. My fingers are already starting to go numb and it's only fall. 
    Hmm... Maybe some skin to skin contact would help get my blood flowing properly again. What do you think? 

    Aww, petname. You always look so cute running around doing your errands, but...
    Are you sure you should be doing all this in your condition? 

    You seem a bit stressed, are you alright?
    _It's all the farmwork..._Aww, petname. You need to take it easy. Someone in your health shouldn't work too hard.
    _It's the disease..._Aww, petname. You're doing an amazing job taking care of it though! I'm sure you'll live a long life despite it.

    Are you always this kind to everyone? Or just me.
    Or... Is it just because I'm your doctor?
    You don't have to put on a fascade around me, petname. I want you to treat me like any normal friend... Or... Potentially more than.
    
    Ugh, this weather would be perfect to open a book and sit next to a fireplace all day. 
    Too bad I have some paperwork to finish up...
    */

