    /*
    Did I hear you sneeze? 
    Well, did you know that holly leaves can be used to treat a variety of ailments, including allergy symptoms?
    Though, their berries can cause quite a few issues. Large quantities often leaving people bedridden. 
    Right, I guess I did get off track. Did you need something for your sneezing? 

    Mmmm... Hot chocolate in this weather would be to die for, wouldn't you agree?
    Though, What really interests me would be a mocha coffee of some sort... I'll have to test that one out later. 

    Hmph, I can't believe it's been almost a year and I still have yet to properly get to know you, petname. 
    Shall we make it a new year's resolution to get to know one another? 

    Make sure you're dripping your faucets and leaving the heat on. 
    Yoba knows the one thing worse than a doctor's pill is a plumber's...

    Hm? Can I help you?
    Sorry, this season's just busy for me and I don't have much time to socialize. 
    I'll make it a mission to get to know you more after cold and flu season's over, promise.

    Listen, I know winter means ample opportunity to make progress in the mines, but please be careful. 
    Though I enjoy your company, having you in one of my hospital beds is far from ideal.

    I guess I should be flattered you came all this way despite the weather, huh?
    Would you like me to fetch a blanket and some hot cocoa for you? It's the least I could do.

    Fresh air is good for the body, but with this weather, spending too much time outside can be dangerous for your health.
    Make sure you don't wander around too much, yeah? 

    Don't take this the wrong way, but please, if I do something that makes you uncomfortable, do tell me.
    There's nothing I hate more than to causing a patient displeasure. 

    You trust me, right? As your doctor, of course...
    I only want what's best for you, petname. 

    %You notice Harvey running his fingers through his hair, clearly stressed. 
    Not now, @. I have a lot of work to finish. 
    ... Actually, I wouldn't mind your company. Maybe I could bounce a few ideas off of you.
    Do you know anything about Polyarthralgia?

    Winter's your off season, right?
    Well, for me it's the opposite... Flu season's in full force this year and paperwork keeps piling up...

    I was hoping you could plant this when spring comes around so it'll be ready for harvest once summer hits.
    Vitamin C's good for the immune system and all. [630] //orange tree

    With how cold it's gotten, I hope your fireplace is cleaned and working properly.
    If you need help, don't hesitate to ask. I'm more than willing to come over and take a look. 
    You'd be surprised on the amount of soot-related injuries I've seen...
    */

